764
01:14:22,161 --> 01:14:25,041
But it's private industry like yours that stands to benefit most...

765
01:14:25,041 --> 01:14:27,761
by moving inside the wire of Commandant Amon Goeth's camp...

766
01:14:27,761 --> 01:14:30,151
No, no, no. Sit, sit. Julian, how are you?

767
01:14:30,151 --> 01:14:31,701
-How are you? -Good to see you, my friend.

768
01:14:31,701 --> 01:14:32,791
Oskar Schindler.

769
01:14:32,791 --> 01:14:34,281
LeoJohn.

770
01:14:38,691 --> 01:14:39,691
Franz, good to see you.

771
01:14:39,691 --> 01:14:41,081
Hello, Oskar. Glad you could join us.

772
01:14:41,081 --> 01:14:43,461
My pleasure. Julius.

773
01:14:43,571 --> 01:14:44,461
How are you? You lost weight.

774
01:14:44,461 --> 01:14:45,451
Only in the shoulders.

775
01:14:45,451 --> 01:14:47,661
Please, everybody, sit down.

776
01:14:48,411 --> 01:14:50,751
How are you doing? Oskar Schindler.

777
01:14:52,731 --> 01:14:53,951
We started without you.

778
01:14:53,951 --> 01:14:56,331
Fine. I miss anything good?

779
01:14:56,601 --> 01:14:58,851
I was explaining to Herr Bosch and Herr Madritsch...

780
01:14:58,851 --> 01:15:01,941
some of the benefits of moving their factories into Plaszow.

781
01:15:01,941 --> 01:15:03,791
I meant the food.

782
01:15:06,431 --> 01:15:10,591
Since your labor is housed on-site, it's available to you at all times.

783
01:15:10,591 --> 01:15:12,731
You can work them all night if you want.

784
01:15:13,171 --> 01:15:16,131
Your factory policies, whatever they've been in the past

785
01:15:16,131 --> 01:15:19,521
they'll continue to be. They'll be respected.

786
01:15:19,731 --> 01:15:22,611
I have to know, where do you get a suit like that?

787
01:15:22,611 --> 01:15:23,601
What is that? Is that silk?

788
01:15:23,601 --> 01:15:25,141
Of course.

789
01:15:26,691 --> 01:15:29,861
Ja. It's... It has a nice sheen about it.

790
01:15:29,861 --> 01:15:30,661
Thank you.

791
01:15:30,661 --> 01:15:31,841
Very nice.

792
01:15:31,981 --> 01:15:36,261
I'd say I'd get you one, but the man who made it is probably dead.

793
01:15:36,261 --> 01:15:38,231
I don't know.

794
01:15:38,231 --> 01:15:40,671
I go to work the other day.

795
01:15:41,401 --> 01:15:43,341
Nobody's there.

796
01:15:43,611 --> 01:15:47,751
Nobody tells me about this. I have to find out. I have to go in.

797
01:15:48,261 --> 01:15:50,261
Everybody's gone.

798
01:15:58,141 --> 01:16:00,951
They're not gone. They're here.

799
01:16:04,311 --> 01:16:06,401
They're mine! Every day that goes by, I'm losing money.

800
01:16:06,401 --> 01:16:09,141
Every worker that is shot costs me money. I have to find somebody else.

801
01:16:09,141 --> 01:16:11,051
We are going to be making so much money...

802
01:16:11,051 --> 01:16:12,341
that none of this is going to matter.

803
01:16:12,341 --> 01:16:14,201
It's bad business.

804
01:16:26,411 --> 01:16:27,811
Thank you.

805
01:16:28,131 --> 01:16:30,041
Leave the bottle.

806
01:16:30,661 --> 01:16:33,181
Take that.

807
01:16:34,081 --> 01:16:37,111
Lena... thank you.

808
01:16:46,181 --> 01:16:49,331
Scherner told me something else about you.

809
01:16:51,391 --> 01:16:53,441
Yeah? What's that?

810
01:16:53,611 --> 01:16:57,761
That you know the meaning of the word "gratitude."

811
01:16:58,871 --> 01:17:00,841
That it's not some vague thing with you...

812
01:17:00,841 --> 01:17:04,341
like it is with others.

813
01:17:05,261 --> 01:17:08,021
You want to stay where you are.

814
01:17:08,411 --> 01:17:11,271
You've got things going on the side.

815
01:17:11,571 --> 01:17:15,431
Things are good.

816
01:17:15,431 --> 01:17:17,441
You don't want anybody telling you what to do.

817
01:17:17,671 --> 01:17:21,771
I can understand all that, you know. L... I know you.

818
01:17:24,141 --> 01:17:29,151
What you want... is your own sub-camp.

819
01:17:34,331 --> 01:17:36,641
Do you have any idea what is involved? The paperwork alone?

820
01:17:36,851 --> 01:17:39,101
You've got to build the thing.

821
01:17:39,101 --> 01:17:41,931
Getting the fucking permits is enough to drive you crazy.

822
01:17:41,931 --> 01:17:44,551
Then the engineers show up, they stand around

823
01:17:44,551 --> 01:17:47,481
they argue about drainage, foundations...

824
01:17:47,481 --> 01:17:49,201
codes, exact specifications, fences four kilometers long

825
01:17:49,201 --> 01:17:50,171
1,200 kilograms of barbed wire...

826
01:17:50,171 --> 01:17:53,571
6,000 kilograms of electrified fences, ceramic insulators...

827
01:17:53,571 --> 01:17:55,491
three cubic meters of air space per prisoner.

828
01:17:55,491 --> 01:17:57,511
I'm telling you, you want to shoot somebody.

829
01:17:57,511 --> 01:17:59,661
I've been through it. I know.

830
01:17:59,661 --> 01:18:02,161
Well, you know. You've been through it.

831
01:18:05,401 --> 01:18:07,991
You could make things easier for me.

832
01:18:11,201 --> 01:18:13,441
I'd be grateful.

833
01:18:46,921 --> 01:18:48,481
Where's Stern?

834
01:18:52,251 --> 01:18:54,441
Goldberg and Chilowicz... make sure I see my cut...

835
01:18:54,441 --> 01:18:59,671
from the, uh, factory owners in this camp...

836
01:18:59,671 --> 01:19:03,141
leaving you to take care of my main account...

837
01:19:03,141 --> 01:19:06,141
the Schindler account.

838
01:19:06,381 --> 01:19:10,231
He wants his independence. I gave it to him.

839
01:19:10,371 --> 01:19:12,901
But independence costs money.

840
01:19:13,281 --> 01:19:15,051
This you understand?

841
01:19:20,261 --> 01:19:21,921
Look at me.

842
01:19:32,481 --> 01:19:35,701
Don't forget who you are working for now.

843
01:19:45,251 --> 01:19:47,641
Jawohl.! -Make sure he stays. He's a slippery bastard.!

844
01:19:47,641 --> 01:19:48,911
Ja. Now, girls, everyone.

845
01:19:55,361 --> 01:19:57,191
-We need more wine. -More wine!

846
01:19:57,851 --> 01:20:00,741
Stand on my friend. Don't let him leave.

847
01:20:22,721 --> 01:20:24,861
Thank you, Herr Direktor.

848
01:20:30,321 --> 01:20:31,501
What are you doing?

849
01:20:31,501 --> 01:20:33,881
What? Scratching my head.

850
01:20:33,961 --> 01:20:35,551
Makes them think we have lice.

851
01:20:35,551 --> 01:20:37,741
Helps make them keep their distance.

852
01:20:38,341 --> 01:20:39,211
-Do you have lice? -Do you have your notebook?

853
01:20:39,211 --> 01:20:42,091
The calendar on my desk has the birthdays of

854
01:20:42,091 --> 01:20:44,471
our SS friends' wives and children.

855
01:20:44,471 --> 01:20:46,161
Don't forget to send something.

856
01:20:46,531 --> 01:20:48,291
Record payoffs to the Main Administration

857
01:20:48,291 --> 01:20:50,061
and Economics Office, the Arm...

858
01:20:50,061 --> 01:20:51,251
Slowly, Stern, slowly.

859
01:20:51,251 --> 01:20:53,841
The Armaments Board, Governor General's Division...

860
01:20:53,841 --> 01:20:56,621
of the Interior and Chief of Police as "fees"

861
01:20:56,621 --> 01:20:58,851
and make them on the first of each month...

862
01:20:58,851 --> 01:21:01,571
as opposed to individual payoffs to our SS contacts.

863
01:21:01,571 --> 01:21:03,671
The list is in the lower drawer of my desk, which you...

864
01:21:03,671 --> 01:21:04,911
"First of month..."

865
01:21:06,441 --> 01:21:09,411
SS contacts: List, lower drawer of my desk, which you handle...

866
01:21:09,411 --> 01:21:13,451
as cash contributions to legitimate charities sent to each official's office.

867
01:21:13,451 --> 01:21:16,131
Dealings with our black market contacts

868
01:21:16,131 --> 01:21:18,591
listed as suppliers in the legitimate ledger

869
01:21:18,591 --> 01:21:19,831
are more complicated. Forget it.

870
01:21:19,831 --> 01:21:21,091
What do you mean, forget it? You can't forget it!

871
01:21:21,091 --> 01:21:23,531
It gives me a headache!

872
01:21:30,511 --> 01:21:31,571
I couldn't get you out of here.

873
01:21:31,571 --> 01:21:32,921
I'll be all right.

874
01:21:33,601 --> 01:21:36,541
Anyway, I'm here almost every week.

875
01:21:36,681 --> 01:21:40,981
I'll look in on you, see how you're doing.

876
01:21:44,971 --> 01:21:47,571
Here, put these in your pocket. Come on.

877
01:21:52,481 --> 01:21:54,561
Herr Direktor, don't let things fall apart.

878
01:21:54,561 --> 01:21:56,161
I've worked too hard.

879
01:22:04,791 --> 01:22:08,801
Thanks for... Good luck.

880
01:22:29,681 --> 01:22:32,501
Achtung, Mutzen ab.!

881
01:22:41,741 --> 01:22:43,111
-Work! -An die Arbeit.!

882
01:22:57,791 --> 01:22:59,201
What are you making?

883
01:22:59,331 --> 01:23:01,151
Hinges, sir.

884
01:23:04,461 --> 01:23:07,981
Ja, I've got some workers coming in tomorrow. Where are they from again?

885
01:23:07,981 --> 01:23:09,761
Yugoslavia, Herr Kommandant.

886
01:23:09,911 --> 01:23:12,011
I've got to make room.

887
01:23:14,591 --> 01:23:17,061
-Make me a hinge. -Yes, sir.

888
01:23:48,561 --> 01:23:50,111
Keep going, you're doing well.

889
01:23:59,331 --> 01:24:01,631
Oh, that's very good.

890
01:24:02,211 --> 01:24:05,841
But I'm a bit confused, and perhaps you can help me.

891
01:24:05,841 --> 01:24:08,251
What I don't understand is that you've been working...

892
01:24:08,251 --> 01:24:13,371
since I think, what, about 6:00 this morning?

893
01:24:14,321 --> 01:24:19,111
Yet such a small pile of hinges.

894
01:24:46,971 --> 01:24:47,941
Oh, Christ.

895
01:24:47,941 --> 01:24:49,541
May I try that, sir?

896
01:24:49,541 --> 01:24:51,791
Check the angle lever. Maybe it's bent.

897
01:24:52,401 --> 01:24:53,492
No, no. You wouldn't hear

898
01:24:53,493 --> 01:24:54,881
a click if it was the angle lever.

899
01:24:54,881 --> 01:24:57,361
Maybe it's the pin. Maybe the pin shaft is greasy.

900
01:24:57,361 --> 01:24:59,451
What did I just say? Here.

901
01:25:01,221 --> 01:25:04,541
Herr Kommandant...

902
01:25:04,621 --> 01:25:06,121
I beg to report

903
01:25:06,121 --> 01:25:10,271
that my heap ofhinges was so unsatisfactory...

904
01:25:10,271 --> 01:25:14,631
because the machines were being recalibrated this morning.

905
01:25:15,691 --> 01:25:18,731
I w-was put on to shoveling coal.

906
01:25:41,281 --> 01:25:42,801
Strange, huh?

907
01:25:49,731 --> 01:25:51,351
Thank you, Muek.

908
01:25:53,231 --> 01:25:56,831
Ah, Lisiek. Don't touch the leather, it's just been oiled.

909
01:25:58,011 --> 01:25:58,491
-Rottenfuhrer. -Oh, for me?

910
01:25:58,491 --> 01:26:01,751
Oh, thank you very much, Herr Direktor.

911
01:26:12,651 --> 01:26:15,331
So the man can turn out a hinge in less than a minute.

912
01:26:15,331 --> 01:26:16,901
Why the long story? Hmm?

913
01:26:45,291 --> 01:26:46,461
Thank you, sir.

914
01:26:46,461 --> 01:26:48,021
You're welcome.

915
01:26:51,171 --> 01:26:53,961
Nobody knows who stole the chicken, hmm?

916
01:26:54,861 --> 01:26:59,381
A man walks around with a chicken and nobody notices this.

917
01:26:59,571 --> 01:27:01,401
Save yourselves.

918
01:27:02,331 --> 01:27:04,501
Tell him about the chicken.

919
01:27:19,491 --> 01:27:21,491
Still nobody knows.

920
01:27:32,451 --> 01:27:36,301
It was you. You committed this crime.

921
01:27:36,301 --> 01:27:36,951
No, sir.

922
01:27:36,951 --> 01:27:38,551
But you know who, though.

923
01:27:38,551 --> 01:27:39,461
Yes.

924
01:27:39,461 --> 01:27:40,801
Who?

925
01:27:42,151 --> 01:27:43,671
Him!

926
01:27:47,621 --> 01:27:48,651
He's very gifted.

927
01:27:48,651 --> 01:27:49,671
Sure.

928
01:27:49,671 --> 01:27:51,071
Bring him over.

929
01:27:53,851 --> 01:27:55,371
Yes, Sir.

930
01:27:56,621 --> 01:27:58,061
Thank you.

931
01:28:03,261 --> 01:28:04,921
Thank you again, Herr Direktor.

932
01:28:04,921 --> 01:28:06,051
You're welcome again.

933
01:28:06,051 --> 01:28:08,671
It's an honor to work for such a great company.

934
01:28:08,671 --> 01:28:09,751
It's great to have you.

935
01:28:09,751 --> 01:28:13,231
I promise to learn everything about enamelware production.

936
01:28:13,231 --> 01:28:14,711
That's great.

937
01:28:25,781 --> 01:28:28,441
Hello? Miss Elsa Krause is here.

938
01:28:28,441 --> 01:28:30,141
I only need five minutes.

939
01:28:30,141 --> 01:28:32,191
She wants to speak to the Herr Direktor.

940
01:28:57,531 --> 01:28:59,421
Yes. He won't see you.

941
01:29:28,731 --> 01:29:30,541
Please, sit down.

942
01:29:34,011 --> 01:29:35,621
Pernod? Cognac?

943
01:29:35,621 --> 01:29:37,541
Uh, no. No, thank you.

944
01:29:37,951 --> 01:29:40,821
So, what can I do for you?

945
01:29:45,591 --> 01:29:47,921
They say that no one dies here.

946
01:29:47,921 --> 01:29:50,591
They say your factory is a haven.

947
01:29:52,921 --> 01:29:54,911
They say you are good.

948
01:29:57,791 --> 01:29:59,491
Who says that?

949
01:30:00,051 --> 01:30:01,811
Everyone.

950
01:30:08,281 --> 01:30:10,921
My name is Regina Perlman, not Elsa Krause.

951
01:30:10,921 --> 01:30:12,841
I've been living in Krakow on false papers

952
01:30:12,841 --> 01:30:14,241
since the ghetto massacre.

953
01:30:14,241 --> 01:30:16,301
My parents are in Plaszow.

954
01:30:16,301 --> 01:30:20,361
Their names are Chana and Jakob Perlman.

955
01:30:20,361 --> 01:30:21,901
They are older people.

956
01:30:21,901 --> 01:30:23,991
They are killing older people now in plaszow.

957
01:30:23,991 --> 01:30:26,741
They bury them up in the forest. Look...

958
01:30:28,581 --> 01:30:30,591
I don't have any money.

959
01:30:30,631 --> 01:30:34,401
I, I borrowed these clothes.

960
01:30:36,321 --> 01:30:38,081
I'm begging you.

961
01:30:38,331 --> 01:30:41,931
Please, please bring them here.

962
01:30:41,931 --> 01:30:43,841
I don't do that.

963
01:30:44,551 --> 01:30:46,301
You've been misled.

964
01:30:46,931 --> 01:30:50,301
I ask one thing: Whether or not a worker has certain skills.

965
01:30:51,641 --> 01:30:53,861
My father is an importer, not a metalworker.

966
01:30:53,861 --> 01:30:55,991
Such activities are illegal.

967
01:30:55,991 --> 01:30:58,311
You will not entrap me!

968
01:30:58,811 --> 01:31:02,361
Cry, and I will have you arrested. I swear to God!

969
01:31:11,521 --> 01:31:13,991
People die. It's a fact of life.

970
01:31:14,261 --> 01:31:16,221
He wants to kill everybody?

971
01:31:16,221 --> 01:31:17,851
Great! What am I supposed to do about it?

972
01:31:17,961 --> 01:31:20,601
Bring everybody over? Is that what you think?

973
01:31:20,601 --> 01:31:23,461
Send them over to Schindler. Send them all!

974
01:31:23,461 --> 01:31:27,261
His place is a haven, didn't you know? It's not a factory.

975
01:31:27,261 --> 01:31:29,391
It's not an enterprise of any kind.

976
01:31:29,391 --> 01:31:32,221
It's a haven for rabbis and orphans...

977
01:31:32,221 --> 01:31:35,061
and people with no skills whatsoever!

978
01:31:37,601 --> 01:31:39,941
You think I don't know what you're doing?

979
01:31:39,941 --> 01:31:43,271
You're so quiet all the time. I know, I know!

980
01:31:43,271 --> 01:31:44,021
Are you losing money?

981
01:31:44,021 --> 01:31:46,351
That's not the point!

982
01:31:46,351 --> 01:31:47,451
What other point is...

983
01:31:47,451 --> 01:31:49,921
It's dangerous! It's dangerous to me!

984
01:31:53,791 --> 01:31:57,221
You have to understand. Goeth is under enormous pressure.

985
01:31:57,221 --> 01:32:00,001
You have to think of it in his situation.

986
01:32:01,101 --> 01:32:03,421
He's got this whole place to run.

987
01:32:03,421 --> 01:32:08,221
He's responsible for everything here, all these people.

988
01:32:09,571 --> 01:32:11,771
He's got a lot of things to worry about.

989
01:32:11,771 --> 01:32:15,271
And he's got the war which brings out the worst in people.

990
01:32:15,271 --> 01:32:17,181
Never the good, always the bad. Always the bad.

991
01:32:18,651 --> 01:32:23,131
But in normal circumstances he wouldn't be like this.

992
01:32:23,131 --> 01:32:23,971
He'd be all right.

993
01:32:23,971 --> 01:32:26,451
There'd just be the good aspects of him which...

994
01:32:27,491 --> 01:32:30,101
He's a wonderful crook.

995
01:32:30,101 --> 01:32:34,461
A man who loves good food, good wine, the ladies, making money...

996
01:32:34,461 --> 01:32:36,181
Killing.

997
01:32:36,951 --> 01:32:39,021
He can't enjoy it.

998
01:32:39,561 --> 01:32:41,701
Bejski told me the other day,

999
01:32:41,701 --> 01:32:45,881
somebody escaped from a work detail outside the wire.

1000
01:32:45,931 --> 01:32:49,151
Goeth lined up everybody from the missing man's barracks.

1001
01:32:49,211 --> 01:32:51,171
He shot the man to the left of Bejski, the man to the right ofhim.

1002
01:32:51,171 --> 01:32:56,001
He walked down the line shooting every other man with a pistol.

1003
01:33:01,961 --> 01:33:03,611
Twenty-five.

1004
01:33:07,901 --> 01:33:09,341
What do you want me to do about it?

1005
01:33:09,341 --> 01:33:10,931
Nothing, nothing.

1006
01:33:11,541 --> 01:33:13,481
We're just talking.

1007
01:33:25,371 --> 01:33:26,721
"Perlman."

1008
01:33:28,531 --> 01:33:30,511
Perlman!

1009
01:33:31,441 --> 01:33:33,081
Husband and wife.

1010
01:33:33,101 --> 01:33:36,941
Jakob and Chana Perlman!

1011
01:33:49,271 --> 01:33:51,611
Have Goldberg bring them over.

1012
01:34:45,081 --> 01:34:48,571
I'm sure this will be better than those rags, Lisiek.

1013
01:34:49,271 --> 01:34:52,971
Herr Direktor, I was just helping Lisiek to find something...

1014
01:34:52,971 --> 01:34:56,411
to clean the stains from the Herr Kommandant's bathtub.

1015
01:34:56,411 --> 01:34:58,641
Go clean it. Pardon me, Herr Direktor.

1016
01:35:02,391 --> 01:35:04,771
You don't have to report to me, Helen.

1017
01:35:05,511 --> 01:35:07,431
You know who I am? Hmm?

1018
01:35:15,901 --> 01:35:17,811
I'm Schindler.

1019
01:35:19,261 --> 01:35:22,141
Of course. L-I have heard and...

1020
01:35:22,941 --> 01:35:25,101
you have been here before.

1021
