-Beans in chunt?

1520
02:24:43,551 --> 02:24:45,101
-Beans are the best part.

1521
02:24:45,101 --> 02:24:47,231
I don't like beans.

1522
02:24:47,451 --> 02:24:51,171
Beans and meat and potatoes and bread.

1523
02:24:51,171 --> 02:24:53,731
That's not the way you make chunt.

1524
02:24:57,481 --> 02:24:59,041
-Eggs in chunt?

1525
02:24:59,041 --> 02:25:00,541
-Yes!

1526
02:25:02,891 --> 02:25:04,261
-I don't like chunt.

1527
02:25:04,261 --> 02:25:07,011
-No, you don't.  -What do you like?

1528
02:25:07,011 --> 02:25:08,891
-I like caviar.

1529
02:25:10,431 --> 02:25:13,371
One day on the fire...

1530
02:26:52,901 --> 02:26:56,101
reissig, fuenfunddreissig

1531
02:26:56,101 --> 02:26:57,651
vierzig

1532
02:26:58,051 --> 02:26:59,991
fuenfundvierzig

1533
02:27:13,311 --> 02:27:15,071
-Where are the list makers?

1534
02:27:15,071 --> 02:27:16,891
-Where are the tables?

1535
02:27:19,521 --> 02:27:23,221
Move the line.!

1536
02:27:38,281 --> 02:27:40,501
Mama, where are we?

1537
02:27:43,971 --> 02:27:46,851
-17, 18, 20... -They're in Auschwitz. The train was never routed here.

1538
02:27:46,851 --> 02:27:49,021
Apaperwork mistake.

1539
02:31:31,271 --> 02:31:33,191
Blick hinunter.!

1540
02:31:35,621 --> 02:31:37,811
Die Hand auf die Schulter.!

1541
02:31:38,241 --> 02:31:39,681
-How old are you, mother?

1542
02:31:39,681 --> 02:31:40,931
-Sixty-eight.

1543
02:31:40,931 --> 02:31:42,091
-Cough for me, mother.

1544
02:31:42,091 --> 02:31:46,591
-They say to fall against the fence is a kindness.

1545
02:31:46,591 --> 02:31:49,371
Don't kill yourself against the fence, Clara.

1546
02:31:49,371 --> 02:31:52,411
If you do, you'll never know what happened to you.

1547
02:31:54,851 --> 02:31:56,171
-How old are you, mother?

1548
02:31:56,171 --> 02:31:57,571
-Sixty-six, sir.

1549
02:31:57,571 --> 02:31:58,641
-Sir?

1550
02:31:58,641 --> 02:31:59,841
-Good morning.

1551
02:31:59,841 --> 02:32:02,721
A mistake has been made. We are not supposed to be here.

1552
02:32:02,721 --> 02:32:04,511
We work for Oskar Schindler.

1553
02:32:04,511 --> 02:32:06,371
We are SchindlerJews.

1554
02:32:06,371 --> 02:32:07,901
-Who is Oskar Schindler?

1555
02:32:07,901 --> 02:32:09,791
-He had a factory in Krakow.

1556
02:32:09,791 --> 02:32:11,561
-Enamelware.

1557
02:32:11,561 --> 02:32:13,821
-A pot maker.

1558
02:32:14,341 --> 02:32:16,541
How old are you, mother?

1559
02:32:20,581 --> 02:32:24,321
You are not the only industrialist who needs labor...

1560
02:32:25,761 --> 02:32:27,761
Herr Schindler.

1561
02:32:28,641 --> 02:32:30,281
I remember earlier this year, IG-Farben ordered...

1562
02:32:30,281 --> 02:32:36,081
a trainload of Hungarians for its chemical factory.

1563
02:32:37,091 --> 02:32:40,241
The train came in through the archway...

1564
02:32:40,931 --> 02:32:45,531
and the officer in charge of the selection went immediately to work...

1565
02:32:46,401 --> 02:32:48,901
and sent 2,000 of them...

1566
02:32:48,901 --> 02:32:51,481
straightaway to Special Treatment.

1567
02:32:53,001 --> 02:32:57,921
It is not my task to interfere with the processes that take place down here.

1568
02:32:59,371 --> 02:33:01,761
Why do you think I can help you

1569
02:33:01,761 --> 02:33:04,351
if I can't help IG-Farben?

1570
02:33:04,351 --> 02:33:07,101
Allow me to express the reason.

1571
02:33:15,911 --> 02:33:18,501
I'm not making any judgment about you.

1572
02:33:19,141 --> 02:33:21,731
It's just that I know that in the coming months...

1573
02:33:21,731 --> 02:33:24,861
we're all going to need portable wealth.

1574
02:33:27,881 --> 02:33:30,531
I could have you arrested.

1575
02:33:30,531 --> 02:33:34,781
I'm protected by powerful friends. You should know that.

1576
02:33:37,991 --> 02:33:41,021
I do not say I am accepting them.

1577
02:33:41,821 --> 02:33:45,431
All I say is, I'm not comfortable with them on the table.

1578
02:33:59,811 --> 02:34:02,611
I have a shipment coming in tomorrow.

1579
02:34:03,071 --> 02:34:06,011
I'll cut you 300 units from it.

1580
02:34:12,651 --> 02:34:16,291
-The train comes, we turn it around. -Mmm, yes, yes.

1581
02:34:16,291 --> 02:34:18,341
-It's yours. -I understand.

1582
02:34:18,341 --> 02:34:20,211
I want these.

1583
02:34:23,491 --> 02:34:26,361
You shouldn't get stuck on names.

1584
02:34:33,411 --> 02:34:37,651
That's right. It creates a lot of paperwork.

1585
02:34:37,651 --> 02:34:39,811
Zoldinger, Ernestina.!

1586
02:34:39,811 --> 02:34:41,571
Waldergrun, Hilda.!

1587
02:34:41,571 --> 02:34:43,651
Waldergrun, Leonora.!

1588
02:34:43,651 --> 02:34:45,091
Laast, Anna!

1589
02:34:45,091 --> 02:34:47,241
Pfefferberg, Mila!

1590
02:34:47,241 --> 02:34:48,771
Dresner, Chaja!

1591
02:34:48,771 --> 02:34:50,691
Dresner, Danka!

1592
02:34:50,691 --> 02:34:52,421
Nussbaum, Sidonia!

1593
02:34:52,421 --> 02:34:54,241
Rosner, Manci!

1594
02:34:54,241 --> 02:34:55,651
Hirsch, Helen.!

1595
02:34:55,651 --> 02:34:58,011
Grosz, Chaja Sara.!

1596
02:35:59,111 --> 02:36:02,691
Danka! Danka! Danka!

1597
02:36:02,691 --> 02:36:05,341
No! No! No!

1598
02:36:08,731 --> 02:36:10,751
Hey.! Hey.! Hey.! What are you doing?

1599
02:36:10,751 --> 02:36:15,101
These are mine! These are my workers! They should be on my train!

1600
02:36:15,561 --> 02:36:18,461
They're skilled munitions workers! They're essential!

1601
02:36:18,561 --> 02:36:20,441
Essential girls!

1602
02:36:23,171 --> 02:36:27,551
Their fingers polish the insides of shell metal casings.

1603
02:36:27,551 --> 02:36:30,951
How else am I to polish the inside of a 45 millimeter shell casing?

1604
02:36:30,951 --> 02:36:33,431
You tell me. You tell me!

1605
02:36:35,811 --> 02:36:37,981
Back on the train!

1606
02:36:38,361 --> 02:36:39,871
Back on the train!

1607
02:38:29,511 --> 02:38:33,051
Under Department "W" provisions...

1608
02:38:33,571 --> 02:38:37,211
it is unlawful to kill a worker without just cause.

1609
02:38:38,021 --> 02:38:40,991
Under the Businesses Compensation Fund...

1610
02:38:40,991 --> 02:38:44,481
I am entitled to file damage claims for such deaths.

1611
02:38:45,091 --> 02:38:48,101
If you shoot without thinking...

1612
02:38:48,101 --> 02:38:51,991
you go to prison, I get paid.

1613
02:38:52,131 --> 02:38:54,371
That's how it works.

1614
02:38:54,371 --> 02:38:55,791
So

1615
02:38:55,791 --> 02:38:59,281
there will be no summary executions here.

1616
02:39:00,291 --> 02:39:04,251
There will be no interference of any kind with production.

1617
02:39:04,771 --> 02:39:06,691
In hopes of ensuring that

1618
02:39:06,691 --> 02:39:09,861
guards will no longer be allowed on the factory floor...

1619
02:39:09,861 --> 02:39:12,441
without my authorization.

1620
02:39:18,051 --> 02:39:21,591
For your cooperation, you have my gratitude.

1621
02:39:23,131 --> 02:39:25,241
Come on, come.

1622
02:39:27,811 --> 02:39:30,111
-Come on, boys, come. -Guck dir mal die Buddeln an!

1623
02:39:55,231 --> 02:39:58,401
No doorman or maitre d'

1624
02:39:58,401 --> 02:40:00,891
will ever mistake you again.

1625
02:40:01,061 --> 02:40:02,871
I promise.

1626
02:40:07,041 --> 02:40:08,631
Itzhak.

1627
02:40:09,791 --> 02:40:11,611
-This is Itzhak Stern, my accountant. Itzhak...

1628
02:40:11,611 --> 02:40:13,251
-You must be Mrs. Schindler.

1629
02:40:13,251 --> 02:40:14,341
-It's a pleasure.

1630
02:40:14,341 --> 02:40:16,041
-Emilie has volunteered to work in the clinic.

1631
02:40:16,041 --> 02:40:17,171
-Very generous of you.

1632
02:40:17,171 --> 02:40:17,731
-I know.

1633
02:40:17,731 --> 02:40:20,321
We need to talk when you have a moment.

1634
02:40:20,611 --> 02:40:23,011
This is my wife, Stern. I don't keep any secrets from my spouse.

1635
02:40:23,011 --> 02:40:26,561
Oskar, please, attend to business. It's much more attractive.

1636
02:40:26,851 --> 02:40:27,811
-Madam. -Hello.  What is it?

1637
02:40:27,811 --> 02:40:30,531
We've received an angry complaint from the Armaments Board.

1638
02:40:30,531 --> 02:40:32,871
The artillery shells, tank shells, rocket casings...

1639
02:40:32,871 --> 02:40:35,241
Apparently all of them have failed quality control tests.

1640
02:40:35,241 --> 02:40:37,251
That's to be expected.

1641
02:40:37,251 --> 02:40:39,651
Start-up problems. This isn't pots and pans. This is a precise business.

1642
02:40:39,651 --> 02:40:40,411
-I'll write them a letter.

1643
02:40:40,411 --> 02:40:41,731
-They're withholding payment.

1644
02:40:41,731 --> 02:40:43,171
Sure, so would I, so would you.

1645
02:40:43,171 --> 02:40:45,601
I wouldn't worry. We'll get it right one of these days.

1646
02:40:45,601 --> 02:40:49,371
There's a rumor you've been going around miscalibrating the machines.

1647
02:40:50,051 --> 02:40:53,471
They could shut us down, send us back to Auschwitz.

1648
02:40:55,421 --> 02:40:58,531
I'll call around, find out where we can buy shells.

1649
02:40:58,531 --> 02:41:01,021
Pass them off as ours.

1650
02:41:01,021 --> 02:41:02,171
I don't see the difference. Whether they're made here...

1651
02:41:02,171 --> 02:41:03,421
-You don't see a difference? I see a difference. -You'll lose a lot of money.

1652
02:41:03,421 --> 02:41:05,251
Fewer shells will be made.

1653
02:41:05,251 --> 02:41:05,801
Stern

1654
02:41:05,801 --> 02:41:09,091
if this factory ever produces...

1655
02:41:09,091 --> 02:41:11,271
a shell that can actually be fired, I'll be very unhappy.

1656
02:41:12,251 --> 02:41:14,551
-Hello, madam. -How do you do?

1657
02:41:27,971 --> 02:41:29,951
How are you doing, Rabbi?

1658
02:41:30,341 --> 02:41:31,901
Rabbi!

1659
02:41:34,441 --> 02:41:36,531
Good, Herr Direktor.

1660
02:41:38,051 --> 02:41:40,031
Sun's going down.

1661
02:41:42,461 --> 02:41:44,441
Yes, it is.

1662
02:41:45,761 --> 02:41:48,091
What day is this? Friday?

1663
02:41:48,091 --> 02:41:49,541
It is Friday, isn't it?

1664
02:41:49,541 --> 02:41:51,071
Is it?

1665
02:41:54,851 --> 02:41:59,161
What's the matter with you? You should be preparing for the Sabbath.

1666
02:41:59,751 --> 02:42:01,371
Shouldn't you?

1667
02:42:08,261 --> 02:42:12,641
I've got some wine. In my office. Come.

1668
02:42:50,931 --> 02:42:54,641
For the seven months it was fully operational,

1669
02:42:54,741 --> 02:42:58,461
Schindler"s Brinnlitz munitions factory

1670
02:42:58,731 --> 02:43:03,001
was a model of non-production.

1671
02:43:03,441 --> 02:43:05,281
During this same period

1672
02:43:05,281 --> 02:43:09,661
he spent millions of reichmarks to sustain

1673
02:43:10,151 --> 02:43:13,501
his workers and bribe Reich officials. Gut Shabbos.

1674
02:43:24,741 --> 02:43:26,711
What?

1675
02:43:27,811 --> 02:43:30,201
Do you have any money, uh, hidden away someplace...

1676
02:43:31,171 --> 02:43:34,361
that I don't know about?

1677
02:43:38,471 --> 02:43:40,281
No.

1678
02:43:45,091 --> 02:43:47,611
Why? Am I broke?

1679
02:43:51,591 --> 02:43:53,401
Well...

1680
02:43:54,821 --> 02:44:00,341
Yesterday morning, at 2.'41 a. M...

1681
02:44:00,931 --> 02:44:04,341
at General Eisenhower's headquarters...

1682
02:44:04,771 --> 02:44:07,221
General Jodl...

1683
02:44:07,301 --> 02:44:11,451
signed the Act of Unconditional Surrender...

1684
02:44:11,521 --> 02:44:17,311
of all German land sea and air forces in Europe...

1685
02:44:17,311 --> 02:44:20,701
to the Allied Expeditionary Force...

1686
02:44:21,091 --> 02:44:25,411
and simultaneously to the Soviet High Command.

1687
02:44:25,761 --> 02:44:29,241
The German war is, therefore, at an end.

1688
02:44:29,731 --> 02:44:31,431
But let us not forget for a moment...

1689
02:44:31,431 --> 02:44:34,681
I think it's time the guards came into the factory.

1690
02:44:38,951 --> 02:44:40,961
Japan, with all her treachery and greed.

1691
02:44:40,961 --> 02:44:43,671
The unconditional surrender of Germany has just been announced.

1692
02:44:44,191 --> 02:44:48,911
At midnight tonight, the war is over.

1693
02:44:50,631 --> 02:44:56,411
Tomorrow you'll begin the process...

1694
02:44:58,721 --> 02:45:01,081
of looking for survivors of your families.

1695
02:45:02,051 --> 02:45:04,701
In most cases, you won't find them.

1696
02:45:05,251 --> 02:45:07,931
After six long years of murder...

1697
02:45:08,131 --> 02:45:11,351
victims are being mourned throughout the world.

1698
02:45:13,401 --> 02:45:15,411
We've survived.

1699
02:45:16,351 --> 02:45:19,711
Many of you have come up to me and thanked me.

1700
02:45:22,301 --> 02:45:24,831
Thank yourselves.

1701
02:45:25,701 --> 02:45:28,291
Thank your fearless Stern...

1702
02:45:28,771 --> 02:45:31,301
and others among you who worried about you...

1703
02:45:31,301 --> 02:45:33,691
and faced death at every moment.

1704
02:45:37,571 --> 02:45:40,251
I'm a member of the Nazi party.

1705
02:45:40,421 --> 02:45:43,101
I'm a munitions manufacturer.

1706
02:45:43,391 --> 02:45:46,011
I'm a profiteer of slave labor.

1707
02:45:46,051 --> 02:45:48,761
I am a criminal.

1708
02:45:49,701 --> 02:45:53,371
At midnight you'll be free, and I'll be hunted.

1709
02:45:55,171 --> 02:45:58,531
I shall remain with you until five minutes after midnight...

1710
02:45:58,531 --> 02:46:01,731
after which time, and I hope you'll forgive me...

1711
02:46:01,731 --> 02:46:04,091
I have to flee.

1712
02:46:06,371 --> 02:46:09,831
I know you have received orders from our commandant...

1713
02:46:09,831 --> 02:46:11,971
which he has received from his superiors

1714
02:46:11,971 --> 02:46:14,941
to dispose of the population of this camp.

1715
02:46:15,331 --> 02:46:17,561
Now would be the time to do it.

1716
02:46:17,561 --> 02:46:20,051
Here they are, they're all here.

1717
02:46:20,671 --> 02:46:23,231
This is your opportunity.

1718
02:46:27,071 --> 02:46:29,521
Or you could leave...

1719
02:46:30,691 --> 02:46:33,091
and return to your families as men...

1720
02:46:33,091 --> 02:46:35,291
instead of murderers.

1721
02:47:15,521 --> 02:47:18,931
In memory of the countless victims among your people...

1722
02:47:19,421 --> 02:47:22,961
I ask us to observe three minutes of silence.

1723
02:48:16,031 --> 02:48:17,411
Thank you, Mr. Jereth.

1724
02:48:17,411 --> 02:48:19,321
Thank you, Mr. Jereth.

1725
02:48:21,381 --> 02:48:23,001
Open wide.

1726
02:48:24,901 --> 02:48:26,881
Thank you, Mr. Jereth.

1727
02:48:44,671 --> 02:48:46,871
Thank you, Mr. Jereth.

1728
02:49:09,981 --> 02:49:13,231
As soon as peace occurs, I want...

1729
02:49:14,981 --> 02:49:17,981
um, I want that cloth distributed to the workers.

1730
02:49:18,141 --> 02:49:20,321
Two and a half meters each.

1731
02:49:20,871 --> 02:49:23,911
Also, each person is to get a bottle of vodka.

1732
02:49:23,911 --> 02:49:26,871
They won't drink it. They know its value.

1733
02:49:26,981 --> 02:49:30,081
Likewise those Egipshi cigarettes we organized.

1734
02:49:30,341 --> 02:49:33,341
It'll be done. Everything you ask.

1735
02:49:52,831 --> 02:49:56,761
We've written a letter, trying to explain things...

1736
02:49:56,871 --> 02:49:58,971
in case you are captured.

1737
02:50:01,161 --> 02:50:03,641
Every worker has signed it.

1738
02:50:13,891 --> 02:50:15,611
Thank you.

1739
02:50:41,671 --> 02:50:43,671
It is Hebrew, from the Talmud.

1740
02:50:43,671 --> 02:50:44,221
It says

1741
02:50:44,221 --> 02:50:48,221
"Whoever saves one life, saves the world entire."

1742
02:51:26,851 --> 02:51:29,341
I could have got more out.

1743
02:51:31,171 --> 02:51:32,851
I could have got more.

1744
02:51:32,851 --> 02:51:33,761
I don't know.

1745
02:51:33,761 --> 02:51:38,051
If I just...  I could have got more.

1746
02:51:38,051 --> 02:51:40,821
Oskar, there are 1,100 people who are alive because of you.

1747
02:51:40,821 --> 02:51:43,181
Look at them.

1748
02:51:44,061 --> 02:51:46,241
If I'd made more money.

1749
02:51:50,111 --> 02:51:53,691
I threw away so much money.

1750
02:51:56,381 --> 02:51:58,681
You have no idea.

1751
02:51:59,491 --> 02:52:00,671
If I had just...

1752
02:52:00,671 --> 02:52:05,111
There will be generations because of what you did.

1753
02:52:05,701 --> 02:52:08,061
I didn't do enough.

1754
02:52:08,161 --> 02:52:10,301
You did so much.

1755
02:52:14,051 --> 02:52:15,861
This car.

1756
02:52:16,801 --> 02:52:18,841
Goeth would've bought this car.

1757
02:52:18,841 --> 02:52:22,901
Why did I keep the car? Ten people right there.

1758
02:52:25,991 --> 02:52:27,681
Ten people.

1759
02:52:29,311 --> 02:52:31,171
Ten more people.

1760
02:52:33,661 --> 02:52:36,791
This pin two people.

1761
02:52:39,591 --> 02:52:41,321
This is gold.

1762
02:52:41,321 --> 02:52:43,201
Two more people.

1763
02:52:43,201 --> 02:52:46,271
He would have given me two for it; at least one.

1764
02:52:46,271 --> 02:52:48,881
He would have given me one, one more.

1765
02:52:51,651 --> 02:52:53,541
One more person.

1766
02:52:55,901 --> 02:52:57,921
A person, Stern.

1767
02:52:59,421 --> 02:53:01,231
For this.

1768
02:53:03,581 --> 02:53:06,881
I could have gotten...

1769
02:53:06,881 --> 02:53:10,971
one more person and I didn't.

1770
02:53:11,941 --> 02:53:14,051
And l-I didn't!

1771
02:54:40,201 --> 02:54:45,501
You have been liberated by the Soviet Army!

1772
02:54:53,151 --> 02:54:54,811
Have you been in Poland?

1773
02:54:54,811 --> 02:54:57,211
I just came from Poland.

1774
02:54:59,231 --> 02:55:01,431
Are there any Jews left?

1775
02:55:06,921 --> 02:55:09,051
Where should we go?

1776
